<?xml version="1.0"?>
<application>
	<name>reorder</name>
	<category>General file manipulation</category>
	<description>swaps columns in a delimited flat file</description>
	<options>
		<option has_argument="0" required="0">
			<name>help</name>
			<short>h</short>
			<long>help</long>
			<description>print this message and exit</description>
		</option>
		<option has_argument="0" required="0">
			<name>version</name>
			<short>V</short>
			<long>version</long>
			<description>print version info and exit</description>
		</option>
		<option has_argument="1" required="0">
			<name>verbose</name>
			<short>v</short>
			<long>verbose</long>
			<description>print verbose messages during execution</description>
		</option>
		<option has_argument="1" required="0">
			<name>delim</name>
			<short>d</short>
			<long>delim</long>
			<description>specifies delimiting string</description>
		</option>
		<option has_argument="1" required="0">
			<name>swap</name>
			<short>s</short>
			<long>swap</long>
			<description>specifies two fields to swap (ex: -s 1,3)</description>
		</option>
		<option has_argument="1" required="0">
			<name>move</name>
			<short>m</short>
			<long>move</long>
			<description>specifies a field to move to a new position\n\t\t\t\t\t(ex: -s 3,1)</description>
		</option>
		<option has_argument="1" required="0">
			<name>fields</name>
			<short>f</short>
			<long>fields</long>
			<description>specifies fields to use to create a new string\n\t\t\t\t\t(ex: -f 3,4,1,5,2)</description>
		</option>
	</options>
	<details>
		<item>the fields param is exclusive of swap and move - if -f and -m or -s are\nspecified, only -f will be used.\n\nexample: reorder -d : -s 1,3 -m 2,4 /etc/passwd\n\nwould swap fields 1 and 3, and then would move field 2 to position 4.</item>
	</details>
	<example><![CDATA[<a href="gzdog.html">gzdog</a> $dtfile |
	<b>reorder</b> -f 3-4,1 -d `<a href="tochar.html">tochar</a> 0xfe` \
	&lt; $wdir/tmp/$$_tmpfile.log]]></example>
</application>
